how do i stop my worrying all the time ok here it is i worry all the time i'm in middle school and it's all about me and my families health i worry about getting sick or getting a disease i really just want to be able to relax and have fun but when i start to i just end up worrying again do i have a anxiety disorder how can i stop worrying and relax like a normal person please help what you're describing sounds like obsessive thinking which is usually accompanied by one or more compulsions with your particular obsession these might be excessive hand washing avoiding contact with objects touched by other people repeated cleaning of floors sinks etc etc the obsession and your compulsive response to it are together known as obsessive compulsive disorder ocd other possibilities include germ phobia or one of several other anxiety disorders i would recommend seeing a mental health professional because the sooner and younger you start dealing with this the more likely you are to overcome it he or she can provide therapies and treatments help you talk out the source s of your anxiety and possibly prescribe medication all designed for your specific psychiatric need middle school can be a very difficult phase of life it certainly was for me i wish you all the best in your fight to free yourself from fear Anxiety Insomnia Obsessive-compulsive personality disorder Bipolar disorder Borderline personality disorder Stuttering Clinical depression Charles Darwin's illness Post-traumatic stress disorder Psychiatry Drug abuse Procrastination Cognitive therapy Psychoanalysis Alcoholics Anonymous Anorexia nervosa Traumatic brain injury Drug addiction Social anxiety Binge eating disorder Mental illness Urinary incontinence Asperger syndrome Adult attention-deficit disorder Hypoglycemia Sigmund Freud Sexual dysfunction Addiction Agoraphobia Chronic fatigue syndrome Transsexuality Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Clomipramine Tourette syndrome Alcoholism Mental Health Act 1983 Diag